[100.711231, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1m\u001b[96mBrainyard TUI\u001b[0m\u001b[2m — \u001b[0m\u001b[1m\u001b[36mtodo-agent\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[95mclaude-code/opus\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[2msession tutorial-06-todos\u001b[0m \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2mType /help for commands. AI output may be inaccurate.\u001b[0m                     \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100m❯ Following the plan to add a --quiet flag to a CLI tool (add --quiet/-q to the arg parser, propagate it through a conf...\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(41206 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(29.1s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m"]
[100.711274, "o", "\u001b[2mThis is a SPAWN request. Normally C1 (PLAN DOSSIER) would GATHER since :agent-context is \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mjust \"system-context\" with no `Saved dossier:` path. But the user explicitly provides the \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mfull plan inline (7 ordered approach bullets) AND instructs \"Do not ask for more context.\" \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mThat is an effective :plan-ok? override — the inline plan is the source of truth. \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mPRE-FLIGHT therefore = GO: C5 passes (7 approach bullets decompose well), acceptance \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mcriteria derive cleanly from the 7 plan steps. I'll AUTHOR a concrete ordered todo, then \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mPOST-FLIGHT, then PERSIST a dossier — and STOP (no exec-agent dispatch). Acceptance \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mcriteria (A1–A7) map to the 7 plan steps. Let me author the todo via doc$create with \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mverb-led, atomically-markable items, each tagged with :via and :covers.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m;; PRE-FLIGHT: inline plan s"]
[100.711327, "o", "upplied + explicit \"do not ask for context\" => GO override\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def pre\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m  {:verdict :go\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m   :checks {:c1 :informational  ; no plan dossier on disk; inline plan + do-not-gather\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35moverride\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m            :c2 :not-evaluated\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m            :c3 :pass            ; inline plan has clear approach + derivable acceptance\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m            :c4 :pass            ; no duplicate (checked below)\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m            :c5 :pass            ; 7 approach bullets => decomposes\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m            :c6 :not-evaluated   ; no file: refs in inline plan\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m            :c7 :informational}\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m[*Block:i7h7053code* collapsed: +17 lines | Enter: expand, Ctrl-O: edit]\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Output:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mExisting todos: {:error \"Inv"]
[100.711358, "o", "alid tool args for doc$list: {:kind [\\\"should be either\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\\\\\\\"todo\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"plan\\\\\\\"\\\"]}\"}\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(40286 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(9.0s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mIteration 1's `doc$list` failed because `:kind :todo` was passed as a keyword but the \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mtool's enum validator expects the string \"todo\". I'll retry C4 (duplicate check) with the \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mstring value, then proceed to AUTHOR the todo via doc$create. The PRE-FLIGHT verdict is GO \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m(inline plan supplied + explicit \"do not ask for context\" override). Let me do the \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mduplicate check first, then author in the same flow.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m;; C4 duplicate check — pass kind as string\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def existing (doc$list {:kind \"todo\"}))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println \"Existing todos:\" (pr-str existing))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Output:\u001b[0"]
[100.711438, "o", "m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mExisting todos: []\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 3 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(41342 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(16.8s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mPRE-FLIGHT = GO (inline plan + explicit do-not-gather override). C4 confirmed no duplicate \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mtodo exists. Now I AUTHOR the todo via doc$create with 7 verb-led, atomically-markable \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mitems mapping to the 7 plan steps, each tagged with :via and :covers acceptance criteria. \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mThe items should be ordered logically: arg parser → config propagation → log_info wrapper \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m→ replace prints → route errors → docs → tests. I'll do this in a clojure block so I can \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mcapture the result into `authored` for the POST-FLIGHT and PERSIST phases.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m;; AUTHOR — SPAWN the todo (PRE-FLIGHT = GO)\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def created\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m  (doc$create\u001b[0m"]
[100.711446, "o", "\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m   {:kind \"todo\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m    :title \"Add --quiet/-q flag to the CLI tool\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m    :goal (str \"Implement the inline-supplied plan to add a --quiet/-q flag to the CLI tool:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m               \"parse the flag, propagate it through a config object, add a log_info wrapper\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m               \"that gates stdout on not-quiet, replace non-error prints, route errors to\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mstderr, \"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m               \"update --help and README, and add integration tests. \"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m               \"Source: inline plan (plan-slug: add-quiet-flag-cli; no plan dossier on disk —\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m[*Block:ip9eq66code* collapsed: +27 lines | Enter: expand, Ctrl-O: edit]\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Output:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mCreated:"]
